\begin_layout Subsection
Treasury Bills
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Obligations to pay a particular amount (par) at the maturity date - which
 comes in a one year, or less.
 No interest is paid prior to the maturity date.
 The bills are sold by a single-auction held weekly.
 The price today is at a discount (compared to the par).
 That discount is expressed in the yield, given by:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
yield=\frac{value-price}{value}\times\frac{360}{days\,till\,maturity}\times100\%
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

