 The difference has many reasons (some market makers are needed) and reflects
 the risks associated with uncertainity and liquidity.
 The yields seen there are extremely low, which corresponds to the COVID
 crysis and the attempts of CBs to stimuate the economy by lowering the
 interest rates.
